{"ID":270253, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"253\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs252.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs254.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 253<\/div>\n  <p class=\"cont\">the present distress? I would answer, &ldquo;Shall there be evil in a city and the Lord hath not done it?&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Earth Now Groaning Under Corruption<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">The earth is groaning under corruption,<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> oppression, tyranny and bloodshed; and God is coming\n  out of His hiding place,<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> as He said He would do, to vex the nations of the earth.<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> Daniel, in his\n  vision, saw convulsion upon convulsion; he &ldquo;beheld till the thrones were cast down, and the Ancient\n  of Days did sit;&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> and one was brought before him like unto the Son of Man; and all nations, kindred,\n  tongues, and peoples, did serve and obey Him.<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span> It is for us to be righteous,<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> that we may be wise and\n  understand; for none of the wicked shall understand;<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> but the wise shall understand,<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> and they that\n  turn many to righteousness shall shine as the stars for ever and ever.<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">It Behooves Us to Be Wise<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">As a Church and a people it behooves us to be wise,<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span> and to seek to know the will of God,<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> and\n  then be willing to do it;<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span> for &ldquo;blessed is he that heareth the word of the Lord, and keepeth it,&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> say\n  the Scriptures. &ldquo;Watch and pray always,&rdquo; says our Savior, &ldquo;that ye may be accounted worthy to\n  escape the things that are to come on the earth, and to stand before the Son of Man.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span> If Enoch,\n  Abraham, Moses, and the children of Israel, and all God&rsquo;s people were saved by keeping the\n  commandments of God,<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span> we, if saved at all, shall be saved upon the same principle. As God\n  governed Abraham, Isaac and Jacob as families,<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span> and the children of Israel as a nation;<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span> so we, as\n  a Church, must be under His guidance if we are prospered, preserved<span class=\"footRef\">19<\/span> and sustained. Our only\n  confidence can be in God;<span class=\"footRef\">20<\/span> our only wisdom obtained from Him;<span class=\"footRef\">21<\/span> and He alone must be our\n  protector<span class=\"footRef\">22<\/span> and safeguard,<span class=\"footRef\">23<\/span> spiritually and temporally, or we fall.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">We have been chastened by the hand of God heretofore for not obeying His commands,<span class=\"footRef\">24<\/span>\n  although we never violated any human law, or transgressed any human precept; yet we have treated\n  lightly His commands,<span class=\"footRef\">25<\/span> and departed from His ordinances,<span class=\"footRef\">26<\/span> and the Lord has chastened us sore,<span class=\"footRef\">27<\/span>\n  and we have felt His arm and kissed the rod; let us be wise in time<span class=\"footRef\">28<\/span> to come and ever remember that\n  &ldquo;to obey is better than sacrifice, and to hearken than the fat of rams.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">29<\/span> The Lord has told us to<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107632\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107632)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107632)\">Amos 3:6<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"foo